<paragraph blockId="58.[189,1400,1731,2004]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<keyLead pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
1. Recurrent vein of fore wing (m-cu) postfurcal (
<figureCitation box="[788,901,1731,1758]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="61.[188,231,1845,1871]" captionTargetBox="[219,1362,295,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-12@61.[188,1398,265,1798]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Fig. 27. Hecabalodes anthaxiae Wilkinson, 1929, ♀ (RMNH). A. Wings. B. Metasoma, dorsal view. C. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514753/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 27A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[913,968,1732,1758]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="72.[189,232,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[219,1363,515,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-90@72.[189,1398,488,1911]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="Fig. 33. Hecabalodes xylophagi Fischer, 1962, ♀ (RMNH). A. Wings. B. Metasoma, dorsal view. C. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514769" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514769/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">33A</figureCitation>
). Radial (marginal) cell of fore wing long; its metacarpus (1-R1) 1.3–1.5 times longer than distance from apex of radial (marginal) cell to apex of wing (
<figureCitation box="[438,552,1802,1828]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="61.[188,231,1845,1871]" captionTargetBox="[219,1362,295,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-12@61.[188,1398,265,1798]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Fig. 27. Hecabalodes anthaxiae Wilkinson, 1929, ♀ (RMNH). A. Wings. B. Metasoma, dorsal view. C. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514753/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 27A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[564,619,1802,1828]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="72.[189,232,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[219,1363,515,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-90@72.[189,1398,488,1911]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="Fig. 33. Hecabalodes xylophagi Fischer, 1962, ♀ (RMNH). A. Wings. B. Metasoma, dorsal view. C. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514769" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514769/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">33A</figureCitation>
). Second radial abscissa (3-SR +SR1) of fore wing always almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[339,452,1837,1863]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="61.[188,231,1845,1871]" captionTargetBox="[219,1362,295,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-12@61.[188,1398,265,1798]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Fig. 27. Hecabalodes anthaxiae Wilkinson, 1929, ♀ (RMNH). A. Wings. B. Metasoma, dorsal view. C. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514753/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 27A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[463,518,1837,1863]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="72.[189,232,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[219,1363,515,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-90@72.[189,1398,488,1911]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="Fig. 33. Hecabalodes xylophagi Fischer, 1962, ♀ (RMNH). A. Wings. B. Metasoma, dorsal view. C. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514769" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514769/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">33A</figureCitation>
). African species ........................................................................................ 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[189,1400,1731,2004]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<keyLead pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
– Recurrent vein of fore wing (m-cu) antefurcal or sometimes interstitial (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1229,1872,1898]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="64.[188,231,1884,1910]" captionTargetBox="[216,1361,293,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-19@64.[188,1398,265,1850]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="Fig. 29. Hecabalodes maculatus Belokobylskij sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (RMNH). A. Wings. B. Metasoma, dorsal view. C. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514759/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 29A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1244,1298,1872,1898]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="68.[189,232,1954,1980]" captionTargetBox="[206,1384,280,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-19@68.[186,1402,261,1907]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="Fig. 31. Hecabalodes radialis Tobias, 1962, paratype, ♀ (ZISP). A. Fore wings. B. Hind wing. C. Metasoma, dorsal view. D. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514765" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514765/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">31A</figureCitation>
). Radial (marginal) cell of fore wing short; its metacarpus (1-R1) not longer than distance from apex of radial (marginal) cell to apex of wing. Second radial abscissa (3-SR +SR1) of fore wing aften more or less evenly curved, but sometimes almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[781,894,1978,2004]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="64.[188,231,1884,1910]" captionTargetBox="[216,1361,293,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-19@64.[188,1398,265,1850]" captionTargetPageId="64" captionText="Fig. 29. Hecabalodes maculatus Belokobylskij sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (RMNH). A. Wings. B. Metasoma, dorsal view. C. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514759/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 29A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[905,959,1978,2004]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="68.[189,232,1954,1980]" captionTargetBox="[206,1384,280,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-19@68.[186,1402,261,1907]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="Fig. 31. Hecabalodes radialis Tobias, 1962, paratype, ♀ (ZISP). A. Fore wings. B. Hind wing. C. Metasoma, dorsal view. D. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514765" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514765/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">31A</figureCitation>
). Asian species ............................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<paragraph blockId="59.[189,1400,265,1197]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<keyLead pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
2. Vertex densely undulately transversely striate with rugulosity between striae (
<figureCitation box="[1203,1318,265,292]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="60.[189,232,1742,1768]" captionTargetBox="[217,1364,285,1672]" captionTargetId="figure-18@60.[190,1400,265,1704]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="Fig. 26. Hecabalodes anthaxiae Wilkinson, 1929, ♀ (RMNH). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head and mesoscutum, dorsal view. C. Head, front view. D. Basal segments of antenna. E. Mesosoma, dorsal view. F. Head and mesosoma, lateral view. G. Hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514751/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 26B</figureCitation>
). First metasomal tergite longer, lorger than its posterior width (
<figureCitation box="[915,1024,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="61.[188,231,1845,1871]" captionTargetBox="[219,1362,295,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-12@61.[188,1398,265,1798]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Fig. 27. Hecabalodes anthaxiae Wilkinson, 1929, ♀ (RMNH). A. Wings. B. Metasoma, dorsal view. C. Metasoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514753/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 27B</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor sheath longer than metasoma (
<figureCitation box="[369,476,335,362]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="60.[189,232,1742,1768]" captionTargetBox="[217,1364,285,1672]" captionTargetId="figure-18@60.[190,1400,265,1704]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="Fig. 26. Hecabalodes anthaxiae Wilkinson, 1929, ♀ (RMNH). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head and mesoscutum, dorsal view. C. Head, front view. D. Basal segments of antenna. E. Mesosoma, dorsal view. F. Head and mesosoma, lateral view. G. Hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514751/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 26A</figureCitation>
). Body length 3.0–6.0 mm. – 
<collectingCountry box="[828,904,335,361]" name="Sudan" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Sudan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[916,979,336,362]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">UAE</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[990,1072,336,362]" name="Yemen" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Yemen</collectingCountry>
.......................................... ............................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Wilkinson, 1929" authorityName="Wilkinson" authorityYear="1929" box="[1039,1399,370,397]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Hecabalodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anthaxiae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1039,1197,370,397]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">H. anthaxiae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wilkinson D. S." box="[1204,1399,370,397]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref68647" refString="Wilkinson D. S. 1929. New parasitic Hymenoptera and notes on other species. Bulletin of Entomological Research 20 (1): 103 - 114. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 000748530002099 X" type="journal article" year="1929">Wilkinson, 1929</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="59.[189,1400,265,1197]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<keyLead pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
– Vertex only densely and distinctly or sometimes finely granulate, without striae (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1321,406,432]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="71.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[235,1349,487,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-78@71.[189,1399,467,1883]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="Fig. 32. Hecabalodes xylophagi Fischer, 1962, ♀ (RMNH). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head and mesoscutum, dorsal view. C. Head, front view. D. Basal segments of antenna. E. Apical segments of antenna. F. Head and mesosoma, lateral view. G. Mesosoma, dorsal view. H. Hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5514767" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5514767/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 32B</figureCitation>
